Information on obtaining the Java Runtime Environment for your System

You will need the Java Runtime Environment (JRE) or the Java Development
Kit (JDK) - version 1.1.7 or higher - to run the Market Analysis GUI Client.
You can obtain a version of the JRE or JDK for Linux, Solaris, or Windows at:

http://java.sun.com/j2se/

Links to JREs (or JDKs) for other operating systems can be found at:
http://java.sun.com/cgi-bin/java-ports.cgi

If you notice that the GUI is a little sluggish, you might want to try
IBM's JRE, which includes a just-in-time compiler.  I've noticed about
a 50% increase (over Sun's JDK 1.1.7 - haven't compared it with 1.3)
in the GUI's performance with this JRE.  It's available for free (as of
1/18/2001) at:

http://www.ibm.com/java/jdk/download/
